	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Proposal: Forum for NES Graphics</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In past discussions, <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=55010#55010" class="postlink">difficulty in attracting artists for collaborations has been cited as a factor</a> in why simple little puzzle games dominate the NES homebrew scene. So I hereby propose a new forum in Category:NES / Famicom called "NES Graphics", in hope of attracting pixel artists to the NES scene and letting people already in the NES scene help each other overcome programmer-art syndrome. Topics would include graphic techniques and tools. (Compare "Graphics" in "Multimedia and Design" section on <a href="http://forum.gbadev.org/" class="postlink">GBAdev</a>.)
<br />
<br />I'd like to hear your thoughts on this idea and gain a consensus before putting on my admin hat and making it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


