	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, pixel art for any kind of platform in general should be OK.. remember there are always tricks like stacking sprites on eachother (or on the background) to give the appearance of more color-depth.  In that sense, graphics for pretty much any kind of tile-based system are still relevant to the NES.
<br />
<br />tokumaru: Once there are a decent amount of posts, then anyone will have a pretty good idea of what kind of stuff gets talked about in there.  Which is also why it's important to try to not scare away the non-programmers, heheh.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


